### EcoSudar API Endpoint Tests
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code or copy to Postman/Insomnia

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### ============================================

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### ============================================
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS (8)
### ============================================

### 1. Register New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "9876543880",
  "password": "password123",
  "user_type": "customer",
  "company_name": "Test Company",
  "address": "123 Test Street",
  "city": "Chennai",
  "state": "Tamil Nadu",
  "pincode": "600001"
}

### 2. Login User (Phone)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543880",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Login User (Email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tekaushst@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Get Current User (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOjEwLCJ0eXBlIjoiYWNjZXNzIiwiaWF0IjoxNzc2MTc0NzQxLCJleHAiOjE3NzYxNzU2NDEsIm5iZiI6MTc3NjE3NDc0MX0.hR6rnoWYY3wfjZMRf6N6A3PYHhBl7fSln-ceLtEoTRQ

### 5. Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 6. Forgot Password (Send OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "9876543210"
}

### 7. Verify OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "9876543210",
  "otp": "1234"
}

### 8. Reset Password (Protected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "new_password": "newpassword123",
  "confirm_password": "newpassword123"
}

### 9. Logout (Protected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### ============================================
### USER MANAGEMENT ENDPOINTS (6)
### ============================================

### 10. Get User by ID (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Get User by Email (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/email/test@example.com
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12. Update User (Protected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "updated@example.com",
  "phone": "9876543211",
  "city": "Mumbai",
  "state": "Maharashtra"
}

### 13. Change Password (Protected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1/password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "current_password": "password123",
  "new_password": "newpassword456",
  "confirm_password": "newpassword456"
}

### 14. Delete User (Protected)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 15. Get User Orders (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1/orders?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### PRODUCT ENDPOINTS (3)
### ============================================

### 16. Get All Products (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?page=1&limit=10

### 17. Get All Products with Filters (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products?product_type=pellets&is_available=true

### 18. Get Single Product (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1

### 19. Get Product Configurations (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1/configurations

### 20. Get Product Configurations with Filters (Public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1/configurations?size=6mm&purpose=Commercial Kitchen

### ============================================
### ORDER ENDPOINTS (4)
### ============================================

### 21. Get All Orders (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 22. Get Orders with Filters (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders?order_status=pending&payment_status=pending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 23. Create New Order (Protected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "delivery_address": "123 Main Street, Apartment 4B",
  "delivery_city": "Chennai",
  "delivery_state": "Tamil Nadu",
  "delivery_pincode": "600001",
  "payment_method": "COD",
  "notes": "Please deliver between 9 AM - 5 PM",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_id": 1,
      "config_id": 1,
      "quantity": 100,
      "size": "6mm",
      "purpose": "Commercial Kitchen",
      "sub_purpose": "Food Processing Dryer"
    }
  ]
}

### 24. Get Single Order (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 25. Update Order Status (Protected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "order_status": "confirmed",
  "payment_status": "paid",
  "notes": "Payment received via UPI"
}

### ============================================
### STATISTICS ENDPOINTS (2)
### ============================================

### 26. Get Order Statistics (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/statistics/orders?days=30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 27. Get Order Statistics with Date Range (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/statistics/orders?from_date=2026-04-01&to_date=2026-04-14
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 28. Get Active Orders (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/statistics/active-orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ============================================
### ERROR TESTING
### ============================================

### Test 404 - Invalid Route
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/invalid-route

### Test 401 - Missing Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me

### Test 401 - Invalid Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### Test Rate Limiting - Register (3 per hour)
# Run this 4 times quickly to trigger rate limit
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rate Test",
  "email": "rate@test.com",
  "phone": "1234567890",
  "password": "test123",
  "user_type": "customer"
}